<body>
<h1>{$node_name}</h1>

<p>The option “My Extension" of the Menu “PBX” let you enable and disable Call Waiting, Do Not Disturb, Call Forwarding and Call Monitor Settings features of your extension.</p>

<div class="hlp_figures"><img src="../modules/{$node_id}/images/hlp_myex_config.png" border="0" />
<p>Figure 1</p></div>
<br />
<p>Select the options you want to enable and then click on "Save Configuration" button. Below a description of each option:</p>
<br />
<table class="inline">
    <tr>
        <th>Name</th><th>Description</th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>Do Not Disturb</td><td>This option avoids incoming calls.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>Call Waiting</td><td>Enable the call waiting feature.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>Call Forward</td><td>Redirect the call to other extension.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>Call Forward on Unavailable</td><td>Redirect the call to other extension when your extension is unavailable.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>Call Forward on Busy</td><td>Redirect the call to other extension when your extension is busy.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>Record Incoming</td><td>Select the behavior of recording incoming calls.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>Record Outgoing</td><td>Select the behavior of recording outgoing calls.</td>
    </tr>
</table>
<br />
</body>
</html>

